
[Richmond?, 13 June 1780. TJs letter to Speaker Harrison, 14 June 1780, q.v., states that Todd had addressed TJ on 13 June asking for indemnification for losses in connection with the proposed settlement at the mouth of the Ohio. Todds letter was transmitted to the Assembly but has not been located (JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 46).]
